I"¬<p>Active cognitive probing techniques may be based on surveys, and is related to the field of preference elicitation. Passive cognitive probing techniques may be based on <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/world-models-reflect-ideological-structures">content generated by the person</a>. Active behavioral probing techniques may be based on <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/affect-reflects-ideological-structures">measuring the reaction of the person in response to a claim</a>. Passive behavioral probing techniques may be based on observing the behavior of the person in the world, without intervention, and infering the belief system which could cause it.</p>
